post_text:
ISD 518 has been notified by the Minnesota Department of Health (MDH) of a positive COVID-19 case within our district. District 518 is following MDH guidelines for this situation and is in close contact with representatives from the organization. Decisions are being made in consultation with MDH. We understand that is may create unease in our community. The district has taken action to clean and sanitize the facility and, together with MDH, will continue to monitor the situation. The information of any person involved in this situation is protected by data privacy laws and will not be released by ISD 518 or any partnered organization.

The recommendation from MDH continues to be if you are showing symptoms (fever over 100 degrees Fahrenheit, sore throat, cough, shortness of breath, headache, diarrhea, or vomiting) stay home and contact your health care provider. You may call the Minnesota Department of Health at (612) 268-4569 with questions or concerns.

The Trojan BPA Masks are here! They arrived much earlier than expected (which is a wonderful surprise) and will be available for sale today (Friday) at the High School from 11-1 (Table will set up in the loop for quick drive up & pick up).

Cash preferred in the exact amount needed (change will not be guaranteed) but checks are also welcome. No credit or debit cards. Masks are $6 each or 5/$20. Supplies are limited. More have been ordered and will hopefully be available before school starts.

Trojan Face Mask Details:
*Two Layer Polyester/Cotton Blend Fabric
* Fabric is treated with an Antimicrobial, Water repellent and anti uv treatments
*Four way stretch fabric
*Reusable and washable up to 30 times
*Wash on Gentle Cycle and Hang Dry #518schools #518whspba

post_text:
Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.

Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

____________________________________________________

El estado de Minnesota está ofreciendo fondos para familias que tienen niños de 5 a 18 años de edad y que reúnen los requisitos para recibir comidas escolares gratis o a precio reducido. El nuevo programa llamado Pandemia EBT(P-EBT), proporcionará hasta 325 dólares por niño que la familia puede utilizar para comprar alimentos nutritivos para la familia y aproximadamente 350,000 niños en Minnesota podrían beneficiarse.

Obtengas más información aquí: www.mn.p-ebt.org

post_text:
This morning we would normally be gathering together to reflect on the past year, have a delicious meal prepared by our WHS cooks, and honor some of our staff. Since we are not able to do that in person, we wanted to make sure and honor those that have worked hard for District 518. Please reach out to your co-workers/fellow teachers if they are on this list - they do need to know that what they do is appreciated!

We would like to thank you for all the great work, concern and commitment to the students of this great district, along with your years of service. Your efforts are not forgotten and you all continue to step up when needed in many different capacities. This is an opportunity to take a deep breath and take care of yourselves a bit. You are appreciated. Again, thank you! #518schools

post_text:
Wednesday, May 27, would have been the annual WMS 8th Grade Awards Program and Dance. We wanted to make sure our students know that even though we are not going to be together, we still are proud to honor this group of our 8th grade class on their achievements.

Each year Mr. Luke presents the President's Award for Educational Excellence to 8th grade students that in the classroom have excelled and worked hard during their WMS years. This award is based on grades 6, 7, 8 and you must meet the following criteria:

• Maintain a Grade Point Average (GPA) of 3.5 or higher all three years
• Score at, or above, 85% on the Minnesota Comprehensive Assessment (MCA) test all three years

Each of these students will receive letters from President Trump and Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos, with this special achievement. Congratulations on an excellent educational journey while at WMS, keep up the great work! We expect to continue to hear great things about you as you enter WHS in the fall! #518wms

post_text:
WHS Class of 2020 Music Dept. Awards Announced!

The Music Department of Worthington High School, announces their annual senior music awards for the Class of 2020. These perennial music awards were voted on by the members of each performing large group within the department respectively and approved by directors Jon Loy (Band), Kerry Johnson (Choir) and Melanie Loy (Orchestra).

This year, nearly 350 students participated in music at Worthington High School. Since all spring concerts were cancelled this year due to the COVID virus, the annual spring awards were formally presented recently at each student’s home by the WHS music faculty and the following award recipients represented a very talented and musical 2020 WHS senior class. Congratulations to all the deserving award winners and best of luck to the Class of 2020! Bravo! #518whs #518whsmusicdept

post_text: Congratulations to members of the Class of WHS 2020 that were recently honored by the Worthington Dollars for Scholars with a scholarship award. Best of luck on your post-secondary journey! #518whs
shared_text:
Worthington MN Dollars for Scholars added 33 new photos to the album: 2020 Worthington Dollars for Scholars Award Recipients.
May 15 at 12:49 PM ·

Worthington Dollars for Scholars is pleased to announce its 2020 scholarship winners. Thirty-two members of the WHS Class of 2020 received $36,000 in scholarships. The highest dollar amount awarded to a single graduating class in the organization’s history.

Since the chapter’s reorganization in 1998, more than $467,000 in scholarships have been awarded to 640 local graduates.

Recipients completed applications, which were anonymously evaluated based upon personal data including employment, extracurricular activities, leadership involvement, unusual circumstances, teacher appraisals, class GPA and ACT scores.

post_text:
Hello, WMS,

Governor Walz has spoken, and we will continue with Distance Learning for the rest of our school year. We are all missing seeing each other at school and being in class with our friends and teachers, but we need to stay healthy so that we can all come back together eventually.

If you feel like you just want to talk to someone, other than the people in your house; contact a teacher, counselor, Principal, para or secretary; any of them would be happy just to talk. We are all on Schoology, email, Zoom, or you can call the school, it is okay to reach out any time. We can even help you Zoom together with a group of friends if you ask.

We are making plans and will let you know about: locker cleanout, iPad turn-in, Yearbooks, and many other details. If you have paper homework to turn in, take it to a school or a lunch site and turn it in so you can get credit. Keep showing up for your Zoom classes, keep doing your schoolwork, we will get through this. #518wms

Mr. Luke

If you feel like you just want to talk to someone, other than the people in your house; contact a teacher, counselor, Principal, para or secretary; any of them would be happy just to talk. We are all on Schoology, email, Zoom, or you can call the school, it is okay to reach out any time. We can even help you Zoom together with a group of friends if you ask.

We are making plans and will let you know about: locker cleanout, iPad turn-in, Yearbooks, and many other details. If you have paper homework to turn in, take it to a school or a lunch site and turn it in so you can get credit. Keep showing up for your Zoom classes, keep doing your schoolwork, we will get through this. #518wms

Mr. Luke

post_text: Let's all read together! Join other Minnesotans in reading this great book! #518commed
shared_text:
District 518 Community Education
April 17 at 10:38 AM ·

Hey Minnesota, let's read together!
One Book | One Minnesota is a new statewide book club that invites Minnesotans of all ages to read a common title and come together virtually to enjoy, reflect, and discuss.

Libraries are essential for connection, and through One Book | One Minnesota, libraries across the state will connect their communities through stories. The program aims to bring Minnesotans closer together during this time of distance and adversity.

The first featured book selection is Because of Winn-Dixie by Kate DiCamillo (Candlewick Press). Here is the link to the book, if you do not have a copy of it at home to enjoy and read along: https://library.biblioboard.com/module/one-book-one-minnesota

Reading and libraries are important to Community Education and all of our students! Join along with other Minnesotans in reading this great book! #518commed

post_text: As we close the first week of Distance Learning throughout Minnesota, some thoughts are foremost at the front of everything we have done and will continue to do in the days ahead. First, thank you to our students. You have been rock stars in moving to a different way of school. Second, thank you to our amazing staff. You continue to roll with changing how to reach your students, have a great attitude about it, and inspire all those around you. Third, to our communities that make up District 518. You have supported the school, staff, and families as they have ventured on a new journey - thank you! Lastly to our parents/guardians and family members of our students. This is not a perfect way to do things. Remember that it is OK to not be perfect. Give yourself grace and move on. Give more hugs than normal to your kids. Cheer them on and cheer them up on occasion. And remember that we are all in this together. Everything we do matters. Take care of yourselves and stay healthy! #518schools

¡Información importante para TODAS LAS FAMILIAS DE PRAIRIE!

Por favor venga a la escuela Prairie mañana (25 de marzo) entre 7 am y 6 pm para recoger los materiales de su niño (s) para la Enseñanza a Distancia. El maestro (a) de su niño ha preparado materiales de aprendizaje para 3 semanas en caso que el cierre de nuestra escuela se extienda por órdenes del Gobernador Walz.

La entrega será en la línea de autos, entrando en el estacionamiento hacia el este del edificio donde está el gimnasio de la escuela.

Procedimientos:
• Siga el circulo de la línea de autos
• Dele el nombre, grado y nombre del maestro (a) de su estudiante a la persona que lo atienda
• Para su conveniencia los materiales serán entregados en su carro—no tienen que estacionarse o entrar a la escuela.

Las tareas terminadas serán entregadas una vez que se reanuden las clases, o el siguiente día de distribución de materiales en caso que se extienda el cierre de las escuelas. Este al pendiente para más información. #518prairie

post_text:
Important Information for ALL PRAIRIE FAMILIES!

Please come to Prairie tomorrow (March 25) between the hours of 7 am and 6 pm to pick up your child’s Distance Learning materials. Your child’s teacher has prepared 3 weeks of learning materials in the event that our closure is extended by Governor Walz.

Pick up will be in the Car Rider Pick Up line in the parking lot East of the Prairie gyms.

Procedure:
• Pull up in the circle
• Give your student name(s), grade level, and teacher name to the attendant
• For your convenience, learning materials will be delivered to your car—you don’t have to park or come in to the building

Completed assignments will be collected when school resumes, or on the next Distribution Day if the closure is extended. Watch for more information.
Your child will be receiving free books from the library that they may keep. See you tomorrow! #518prairie

post_text:
Take Ms. Doyle’s Seven Day Drawing Challenge
Use whatever materials you have at home. Be creative!
Day 1: Draw a picture of your future self. What might you look like?
Day 2: Hide a favorite toy, then draw a treasure map to find it. Have a friend or family member follow the map to the hidden toy.
Day 3: Draw a design for a $3 bill. Whose face will be on it?
Day 4: Draw your dream home. Use lots of details.
Day 5: Draw a cat playing a sport.
Day 6: Draw a group of robots having a party.
Day 7: Take two of your favorite animals and combine them to make a new animal. #518WMS

post_text: Lanae was so excited to see the kids yesterday! Meals for youth 0 - 18 and is similar to the Summer Food Program, it does not matter what school you attend, you will be fed. Youth will not be asked for a student ID, where they go to school, lunch pin number or other information. They just need to show up. Youth will receive a grab and go lunch that will have something for breakfast the next morning as well. One meal package per child that shows up. Lanae made sure to tell the kids that they can come back everyday and was a loving example of what Worthington does best in just being kind. We're in this together! #518schools

post_text: Many changes that never seemed possible have happened in a matter of days. Very important announcements and adaptations have occurred in short order with the focus on what is best for all of our kids and staff, along with our communities that make up District 518. We feel like everyone is needing some familiar faces doing fun things that students might recognize and enjoy in the coming days - we have one this afternoon with Mrs. Knips from Prairie Elementary, along with Trojan News interviews. Please take the time to share these posts, videos, activities with your kids. Share with us pictures and stories, because quite frankly we miss all those faces, too. We got this! We're all in this together! Go Trojans! #518schools
